dct_description_sm: Alternate title: Karenko. In upper left margin: Formosa city plans 1:7,500. Polyconic projection. Relief given by form lines and spot elevations. Place names are transcribed according to the modified Hepburn (Romaji) System. With a glossary. Name has been changed to Hua-lien [Hualien]. Compiled in 1945 from aerial photography dated October, 1944, by photo-planimetric methods and by reference to Formosa 1:25,000, A.M.S. Sheet 2418-IV NW. Relief given by form lines and spot elevations. Military grid. Classified roads and trails, railroads, and areas of vegetation and cultivation are shown. Some points of interest are named. Marginal maps and diagrams: Index to boundaries -- Coverage diagram. With a glossary. Place names are transcribed according to the modified Hepburn (Romaji) System. AMS 1. South Decimal Degree 23.966667. North Decimal Degree 24.000000. East Decimal Degree 121.633333. West Decimal Degree 121.583333.
dct_publisher_sm: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1945.
